From 58d6fe4e2ed7c82a9cc847c934d05cdcc1414167 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 06:26:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 23/23] UI rebuild stage 2: mode strip + job-card landing
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CommandShell: render a per-job ModeStrip across the top of the workspace —
the job's member tabs become mode pills, so the 8 KEYS / 10 READ duplicate
tabs collapse into one job screen instead of N drawer entries.

App: add a JobCards hero to the Diagnose landing (the six job doors as
'what are you trying to do?' cards reading labels from the shared model),
gated behind a new DumpsTabV2 onOpenTab prop so existing DumpsTab tests
render unchanged. MarrySyncTab gets a stable marry-sync-tab root testid.

Tests: update the nav drift-guards to the job-flow model — rail doors open
jobs (mode-strip assertion), keyxfer reached via KEYS door + mode pill.
15 nav tests green; the 7 pre-existing suite failures (fixtures/OCR/SEC16,
verified on a clean tree) are untouched by this change.
